{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-8470].
  {panel}

It would be nice if the number of ancestors displayed in email notifications (both watches and daily email updates) were configurable similar to the General Administration's "Number of Ancestors to Show in Breadcrumbs" option.  In many cases, this would make it much more clear what content is being modified without having to navigate to the wiki to to see the full breadcrumbs chain.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-8469].
  {panel}

We would like the ability to limit the number of attachments that can be attached per page.  We would like the ability to set this permission on a space by space basis.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-8458].
  {panel}

On a busy site where users comment and edit a lot, you end up with hundreds of pages that you are subscribed to. At some point, while cleaning up, it would be nice to be able to select a bunch of pages (via checkboxes perhaps) and then click on a button that says "Unwatch all selected pages" or something to that effect.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-8448].
  {panel}

Add a feature that allows administrators to register for an email notification of the registration of new users within the Confluence instance. This would allow open registration by users, but would also allow the administrator to perform group assignments as soon as new users were added to the system.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-8446].
  {panel}

I've just had a customer trying to implement an SSO Authenticator.

He followed this page http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Understanding+User+Management+in+Confluence to this page: http://opensource.atlassian.com/seraph/sso.html which was not completely helpful.  In particular it doesn't contain any Confluence specific information, unlike this page: http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DEV/Single+Sign-on+Integration+with+JIRA+and+Confluence

I have now added a link from the User Management Overview page to the SSO for JIRA and Confluence page, which will hopefully be helpful for future customers, but it's still a little confusing.  In particular nothing really covers how to plug in logging out from SSO.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-8440].
  {panel}

When you type a newline in the Rich Text Editor (starting a new paragraph), and then hit the backspace key (removing the newly created paragraph), the editor loses context and jumps to the top of the page. This is disconcerting when you are editing at the bottom of a very large page, as you need to scroll back down to find the place where you were editing.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-8432].
  {panel}

It would be awesome if the feeds could support RFC-4685* (Atom Threading Extensions) enabling readers to be able to tell if comments have been added to a page. Apache Abdera** could be used to implement this (and more generally improve Atom support).

* http://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc4685.txt
** http://incubator.apache.org/abdera/

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-8429].
  {panel}

Steve provided a patch for this:

--- confluence-orig/confluence/src/java/com/atlassian/confluence/rss/DefaultFeedBuilder.java    2006-08-28 15:35:20.000000000 +1000
+++ confluence/confluence/src/java/com/atlassian/confluence/rss/DefaultFeedBuilder.java 2006-10-09 10:59:32.000000000 +1000
@@ -71,6 +71,11 @@
                     entry.setAuthor(getUserFullName(entity.getLastModifierName()));
                     entry.setPublishedDate(entity.getLastModificationDate());

+                    // This is site-unique, but not global.  We could add the
+                    // server domain here.
+                    String uri = "urn:atlassian.com:" + entity.getId();
+                    entry.setUri(uri);
+
                     entry.setCategories(renderer.getCategories(item));
                     entries.add(entry);
                 }

We need to change it slightly to use (preferably) the server ID or (alternatively) the server base URL instead of "atlassian.com".

I'd suggest a URI of 'urn:atlassian:confluence:<server-id>:<entity-id>'.

