For us it would be very useful to have the information of the "To:" and the "CC:" field of the email envelope for email archived in Confluence.

Use case: We are not just forwarding email to the email address used for mail archiving, but use the Confluence email box as a BCC: when sending messages out. For incoming messages, we prefer Redirect (aka "Bounce") or direct IMAP copying over Forwarding email. All these operations keep the mail envelope, including the "To:" and "CC:" fields of the email intact. Thus we would like to have this information also in Confluence. 

Currently, we have to go back to the email box of the person who sent or received the email once we have found the interesting email in Confluence in order to get recipient information, which is tedious and error-prone. Furthermore, the email may well have been deleted in the mean time, destroying this important piece of information altogether.

