I stumbled across IBM's QEDWiki product and while it still seems very much demoware, one feature that stuck out as being pretty cool and immediately useful for Confluence was the ability to drop Google Gadget components right onto the wiki pages (especially the way it puts a search form and just lets you use Google's search to pick a gadget).  So it would be great if something like this were implemented in Confluence.

http://services.alphaworks.ibm.com/qedwiki/

(And also on a more general note, it would be great to know what Atlassian's plans are for incorporating/competing with the newer wave of mashup servers that are on the horizon.)

